# Supabase & Database Patterns

## Client Architecture

- **Server-side:** `supabaseAdmin` from `@/lib/supabase` — uses service role key, bypasses RLS
- **Client-side:** `createSupabaseClient(accessToken?)` — respects RLS, uses anon key
- The admin client is lazy-initialized via a `Proxy` to avoid throwing during Next.js build-time page data collection. Don't change this pattern.

## Query Patterns

```typescript
// Single row — always check error AND data
const { data, error } = await supabaseAdmin
  .from("extracted_tasks")
  .select("*, transcript:transcripts(*)")
  .eq("id", taskId)
  .single();

if (error || !data) throw new Error(`Task not found: ${taskId}`);

// Insert with return
const { data, error } = await supabaseAdmin
  .from("extracted_tasks")
  .insert({ transcript_id, extracted_title, status })
  .select("id")
  .single();
```

## Column Naming

Database uses `snake_case`, TypeScript uses `camelCase`. Map at the service boundary:

- DB: `extracted_title`, `inferred_assignees`, `missing_context`, `jira_issue_key`
- TS: `title`, `inferredAssignees`, `missingContext`, `jiraIssueKey`

## Config Keys

Runtime config lives in the `pipeline_config` table. Always use `CONFIG_KEYS` from `lib/types/index.ts`:

```typescript
import { CONFIG_KEYS } from "@/lib/types";
// CONFIG_KEYS.CONFIDENCE_AUTO_CREATE_THRESHOLD
// CONFIG_KEYS.JIRA_PROJECT_ROUTES
```

## Tables

| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `transcripts` | Ingested transcripts with provider, status, metadata |
| `extracted_tasks` | AI-extracted tasks with confidence, priority, Jira state |
| `task_status_history` | Audit trail of all task state transitions |
| `pipeline_config` | Runtime config (thresholds, routes, providers) |
| `users` | Team members with Google/Jira/Slack IDs |

## Migrations

- Files in `supabase/migrations/` with numeric prefix (e.g., `005_add_feature.sql`)
- Apply locally with `supabase db reset`
- Test against local Supabase before committing
